<Link id="l00010" /><CodeLine lineNumber="10"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// estimation for LLVM-IR. This analysis uses the services of the codegen</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00011" /><CodeLine lineNumber="11"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// to approximate the cost of any IR instruction when lowered to machine</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00012" /><CodeLine lineNumber="12"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// instructions. The cost results are unit-less and the cost number represents</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00013" /><CodeLine lineNumber="13"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// the throughput of the machine assuming that all loads hit the cache, all</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00014" /><CodeLine lineNumber="14"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// branches are predicted, etc. The cost numbers can be added in order to</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00015" /><CodeLine lineNumber="15"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// compare two or more transformation alternatives.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00016" /><CodeLine lineNumber="16"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//</span></CodeLine>
